<title>UK: Ipeco chairman may buy rest of company.</title>
<headline>Ipeco chairman may buy rest of company.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-03-10</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ipeco Holdings Plc said on Monday that its chairman Chris Johnson might buy the outstanding 32 percent of the ordinary shares of Ipeco not already owned by Johnson and his family interests.  </p>
<p>Ipeco, which designs and manufactures specialist products for the aerospace and engineering industries, said the proposal valued each outstanding share in Ipeco at 90p.</p>
<p>Under the terms of the proposal, shareholders would be entitled to receive a final dividend of 2.3p for the year ended December 31, 1996.</p>
